# Backend (Go)

## Layout

- `cmd/server/` - application entry
- `internal/` - `handler`, `service`, `repository`, `model`, `server`, etc.
- Root `e2e/*_test.go` - Go tests co-located with E2E package (not Playwright)

## Code

- ASCII only in source (see `core.mdc`).
- Prefer clear handler -> service -> repository boundaries; handle errors explicitly.

## Tests

- Go tests: `*_test.go` next to packages (e.g. `internal/handler/auth_test.go`).
- Run: `go test ./...` from repo root, or scoped package path.

## Doc and test sync

- Backend behavior or API changes: update colocated `*_test.go` and any design docs that describe the contract; full matrix: **Doc and Test Sync** in `workflow.mdc`.

## Not in scope here

- Vue/CSS and browser E2E live under `frontend/` and `e2e/browser/`; follow those rules when editing those paths.
